      <div class="step screensteps-section screensteps-depth-1" id="insert_link" data-step-uuid="4361DFB2-995E-43BA-AA70-872B7A242109">
    <h2 id="insert_link" class="step-title screensteps-heading">Insert Link</h2>
        <div class="image screensteps-image">
      <a href="https://media.screensteps.com/image_assets/assets/004/057/144/original/c7954e3e-f025-4870-8fae-d79d00d6c308.png" class="screensteps-image-zoom" target="_blank" rel="nofollow noopener noreferrer">
        <img src="https://media.screensteps.com/image_assets/assets/004/057/144/medium/c7954e3e-f025-4870-8fae-d79d00d6c308.png" srcset="" alt="Insert Link" height="363" width="855">
      </a>
  </div>
 
      <div class="step-instructions screensteps-textblock">
  <div id="text-content_916B1120-221C-0135-AF05-22000B5A851D" class="text-block-content">
    <p>In the Rich Content Editor, place your cursor where you wish to insert your file. You can <a href="/t5/Instructor-Guide/How-do-I-create-hyperlinks-to-course-group-and-user-files-in-the/ta-p/959" target="_blank">add links to course, group, or user files</a>. The name of the page will appear in the Rich Content Editor and flash yellow. Then the name will turn blue, indicating it is a link.</p>
  </div>
</div>
 
  </div>

